evelopers have chosen to also use Linux as their local work computer.  We will discuss hosting servers a little later on this page, but for now we will consider Linux as a local development computer.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Linux of course can be installed on PC\'s and Macintoshes.   It can be installed in a virtual machine on either of those platforms.   It also can run native on Windows using <a href=\"https://cygwin.com\">Cygwin</a> which gives an existing Windows user the ability to use both Windows apps and Linux apps interchangeably.   That also eases the Linux learning curve.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>MacOS is based on Unix and the Mac Terminal app depends on Unix (Linux) shells for line mode interactive commands.   There are many different shells available to choose from, but the most commonly used one in my experience is BASH.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you choose to run Linux as your native OS then you will almost always a graphical user interface.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Windows</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With Windows you naturally have a graphical interface include Windows Explorer,  a web browser like Edge, an interactive command line tool like PowerShell or cmd.exe.   Using your browser there are applications galore that you can download and install.   </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In addition as mentioned above you can also install <a href=\"https://cygwin.com\">Cygwin</a> and get lots of Linux goodies as well.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Macintosh</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As mentioned above MacOS is really UNIX under the covers.   The Terminal window runs many different UNIX shells.   Many common development tools are available for download and install and ready for use.     </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, since Terminal gets you into the core of UNIX there are many UNIX, and Linux package managers available that will let you install just like you are in Linux.  Homebrew is one option.   Just Google \'<a href=\"https://duckduckgo.com/?hps=1&amp;q=package+managers+for+mac&amp;ia=web\">package managers for mac</a>\'</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Web hosting servers</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Most servers are virtual machines in a cloud server farms.   These are almost always headless meaning there is no display and keyboard.   You must access  these using some form of secure shell.   Checkout a google of \'<a href=\"https://duckduckgo.com/?q=ssh&amp;t=osx&amp;ia=web\">ssh</a>\'.   ssh and many programs that use it require secure certificates to be generated and installed on your local machine.  I will have a whole \'How to\' page dedicated to secure networking. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How about you? </h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Give all of those options you probably already have a development platform of some sort and it\'s now time to talk about it.     I need to know about your setup, your needs, and your questions.    I have a \'Your development setup\' challenge page that you can use to tell me all about it.   So, go there and tell me.   </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Development platforms','','inherit','closed','closed','','175-revision-v1','','','2024-02-15 19:53:35','2024-02-15 19:53:35','',175,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?p=177',0,'revision','',0),
(178,1,'2024-02-15 20:03:10','2024-02-15 20:03:10','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once you have read some of this site it is good to put some of that to a test with a challenge.    There are often several paths that will get you to one of these challenges.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When you complete a challenge tell me what you learned and what questions you still have.   For now, we can do that through email and later we can get more formal.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Please make sure that you report your experience.</strong>  To do this, create an email to <a href=\"mailto:MichaelKentBurns@gmail.com\">MichaelKentBurns@gmail.com</a>.  Start your email by copying the text of the challenge into your message.   Make the subject of your email the title of the challenge (from the top of the page).  Then as you follow the steps, simply insert your comments, questions, and problems encountered.   Complete the email with a summary of what you learned.    </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So, dive in:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/challenge-tell-me-about-yourself-so-i-know-how-i-can-help-you/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"181\"><strong>Tell me about yourself </strong>so I know how I can help you.</a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/challenge-tell-me-about-your-development-setup/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"184\"><strong>Tell me about your development setup</strong>,</a> what you already can do, and what you want to be able to do.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/challenge-setup-your-own-github-account-and-install-desktop-github-app/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"187\"><strong>Setup your own GitHub account</strong> and install Desktop GitHub app.</a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/challenge-capture-a-tutorial-project-in-a-github-repository/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"222\"><strong>Take any development challenge </strong>and record your work in a GitHub repository.</a> </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Lots more to come... </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Take a challenge','','publish','open','closed','','take-a-challenge','','','2024-06-29 17:39:08','2024-06-29 17:39:08','',2,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?page_id=178',0,'page','',0),
