(421,1,'2024-05-07 12:45:55','2024-05-07 12:45:55','<!-- wp:group {\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:group {\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:gallery {\"linkTo\":\"none\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"flex\",\"flexWrap\":null}} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\"><!-- wp:image {\"id\":169,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/MichaelAtWork-1024x768.jpeg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-169\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Michael</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":353,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/work-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-353\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Philémon</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></figure>\n<!-- /wp:gallery --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Software development freelancing...</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are many locations around the globe that are hotspots for software development.   If you happen to live in one of those places, jobs can come looking for you.   But there are many places around the world that have little or no jobs in this field.  In those places you need some extra skills to get and keep work, but it can be done.  This site is a place to find help and to build community of fellow developers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Learn a little about me and why I am developing this site on my <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/about-michael/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"22\">About page...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Welcome</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My intention with this main page is to tell a story of a journey that you might be on.  I\'ll try to keep it pretty brief and include \"Learn more...\" links so you can dive deeper as you need.   Hopefully you will find yourself on this journey and find where you are in the story.  When you do, I invite you to contact me.  My intention is that I can help guide you along.   I hope that this will become a community of like minded people.  I invite you to help me understand your needs and together we will keep you moving.  No tricks or fees are involved.   See my <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/about-michael/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"22\">About page</a> for that background.  If you have questions or comments along the way please <a href=\"mailto: MichaelKentBurns@gmail.com\">email me</a>.   This site is a work in progress and I intend to develop it to meet the needs of my readers. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Developing your skills</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While traditional full time employment brings a degree of long term job security, freelancers need to keep their current skills fresh in order to stay relevant.  High tech work is constantly changing with new fields opening up almost daily.  Those new fields often have a higher demand for skilled individuals.  Being willing and able to add new skills will increase your chances of finding work and better pay.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Front end web</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The World Wide Web is a rapidly evolving place, and it is a challenging field to stay fresh in.   Sometimes there are dramatic shifts in interactive technology.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/front-end-web/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"49\">Learn more about front end work...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Back end web</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Back end technologies don\'t change as fast as front end, but...</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/back-end-web/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"52\">Learn more about back end work...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Full stack</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On the surface full stack development is just front end and back end, but there is more to consider...</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/full-stack/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"55\">Learn more about putting it all together...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Working globally</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With the advent of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open-source_software\"><strong>open-source software</strong></a> there arose the need to have world wide access to the source code for the many projects.   <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Git\"><strong>Git</strong></a> is the source control tool invented for Linux development.  <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GitHub\"><strong>GitHub</strong></a> is a web interface for software development which uses Git for the source control features, and describes itself as collaborative version control.   It not only allows you to manage your own projects but lets you share them.  Furthermore it lets you explore a vast galaxy of other projects that you can learn from, and in some cases contribute to.  That is a great way of building your reputation. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/?page_id=59\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"59\">Learn more about how software is developed globally...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Let\'s get acquainted so I can figure out how I can begin to help you. </h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Please take the first challenge to tell me about yourself.  Once we get acquainted I can learn about your needs and desires and continue to develop this site to help you move forward.   I can also get some feedback from you on what is helpful and what is not so much.  Eventually, I would like you to consider being more actively involved in making this site a place where you can help others and learn from them too. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/challenge-tell-me-about-yourself-so-i-know-how-i-can-help-you/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"181\">Take the challenge of introducing your self.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Let\'s consider your development environment</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you are reading this you are probably far enough into web development that you have at least a starter machine and programs to get the work done.    I have a summary of development platforms that you should read to consider what you have, what you might need to move forward.   At the end of that I\'d like to know what you have and what you think you might need.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/development-platforms/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"175\">Learn more about development platforms..</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Take a challenge to <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/challenge-tell-me-about-your-development-setup/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"184\">tell me about your current development setup...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><img class=\"wp-image-420\" style=\"width: 50px;\" src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/New.jpg\" alt=\"\">Software development freelancing activities</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>According to <a href=\"https://www.dictionary.com/browse/activity\\\">Dictionary.com an activity</a> is </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>the <strong>state</strong> or quality of <strong>being active</strong>:</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><em>There was not much activity in the stock market today. He doesn\'t have enough physical activity in his life.</em></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>a specific deed, action, function, or sphere of action</strong>:<em>social activities.</em></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So, if you want to be a software development freelancer you need these kinds of activities:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Learning</strong>: gaining the knowledge to understand. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Training</strong>: practicing and getting evaluated and coached.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Hiring</strong>: finding a job and establishing a contract.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Planning your work:</strong> figuring out how you are going to do the work, when, and reporting your plan.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Equiping</strong>: getting the tools and platforms needed.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Developing</strong>: building, completing, testing and documenting.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Delivering</strong>: handing it over to your client.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Getting paid</strong>: completing the contract, satisfying the client, and getting the pay you have earned.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Rinse and repeat.</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You <strong>can\'t</strong> do these things by yourself!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>A <strong>learner</strong> needs a <strong>teacher</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>A <strong>trainee</strong> needs a trainer or <strong>mentor</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>A <strong>freelancer</strong> needs a <strong>client</strong> with a <strong>job</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>A <strong>planner</strong> needs many things:  decomposition, stages of work, planning, documenting, reviewing, coordinating...</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Equipping</strong> requires a <strong>source</strong> of tools, platforms, and process knowledge to be ready to do the job.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Developing</strong> is a whole process in itself, covered elsewhere on this site.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Delivery</strong> requires a <strong>repository</strong> to document your process and contain your deliverables so they can be used by the client or others.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Getting paid</strong> requires coordination with the client, an escrow agent, a funds transfer agent, and your bank.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Rinse and repeat</strong> requires <strong>learning</strong> from one job and the <strong>courage</strong> and <strong>determination</strong> to start all over again. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>You can do this!</strong>  This site will lead you to all of these things and you can be a success. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><img class=\"wp-image-420\" style=\"width: 50px;\" src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/New.jpg\" alt=\"\">The internet to the rescue!</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So, where do you find all of these people and things?  There are web based platforms that can supply all of these.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Teaching platforms</strong>: Wikipedia, the WWW, <strong>this site somewhat.</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Training platforms</strong>: FrontendMentor, CodingBootCamp?, <strong>this site</strong>!, Discord, Slack.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Freelancing platforms</strong>: Upwork.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Planning platforms</strong>: Agile alliance, ?</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Equipping platforms</strong>: Google Play, AppStore, Linux \'apt get\', homebrew, many commercial sites. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Development platforms</strong>: GitHub, GitLab, Jira ? </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Delivery platforms</strong>: GitHub, GitLab.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Payment platforms</strong>: Upwork, Payoneer, your bank, mobile apps.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Encouragement platforms</strong>: <strong>this site! </strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Finding work as an individual</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are a number of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Freelancer\">freelance</a> marketplaces online.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.upwork.com/freelance-jobs/\">Upwork</a> is one we recommend.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/finding-work/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"79\">Learn more about freelancing work...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Working as part of a team</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Because of the rapid pace of technology development and market requirements, most web and application development is done by integrated teams.  No one person can do it all themselves. It takes a team of specialists working individually and cross discipline to be successful. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A team can take on big jobs that a single person cannot do.   This presents opportunity for the individual developer.  Once you understand how a team can work together you can find the best place to contribute.   But while you are doing what you already know how to do, you will also learn something about the rest of the team and the roles they fill.   And you will find avenues to learn new skills while you build team skills.   </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/working-in-a-professional-team/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"149\">Learn more about working as part of a larger team ...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Development platforms</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Doing web development work as an individual can be done with most any computer running Windows, Linux, or Macintosh.   You most likely already made a choice and are doing work.   However, as you move into full stack work, or start working as part of a team it will get more complex.   It is worth considering the options again. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So, take a moment to<a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/development-platforms/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"175\"> learn more about development platforms...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Accepting challenges to put your learning to work.</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You may have already encountered a prompt to accept a challenge as you have read this far.  If so, good for you.   I will continue to add more challenges to keep you moving forward.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Learn more from the <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/take-a-challenge/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"178\">complete list of challenges...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to do many things related to this work</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I continue to develop <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/how-to/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"108\">how to pages on simple and more advanced topics.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Latest Posts</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:latest-posts {\"align\":\"center\"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','2-revision-v1','','','2024-05-07 12:45:55','2024-05-07 12:45:55','',2,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?p=421',0,'revision','',0),
(423,1,'2024-05-07 12:48:28','2024-05-07 12:48:28','<!-- wp:group {\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:group {\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:gallery {\"linkTo\":\"none\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"flex\",\"flexWrap\":null}} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\"><!-- wp:image {\"id\":169,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/MichaelAtWork-1024x768.jpeg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-169\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Michael</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":353,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/work-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-353\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Philémon</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></figure>\n<!-- /wp:gallery --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Software development freelancing...</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are many locations around the globe that are hotspots for software development.   If you happen to live in one of those places, jobs can come looking for you.   But there are many places around the world that have little or no jobs in this field.  In those places you need some extra skills to get and keep work, but it can be done.  This site is a place to find help and to build community of fellow developers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Learn a little about me and why I am developing this site on my <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/about-michael/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"22\">About page...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Welcome</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My intention with this main page is to tell a story of a journey that you might be on.  I\'ll try to keep it pretty brief and include \"Learn more...\" links so you can dive deeper as you need.   Hopefully you will find yourself on this journey and find where you are in the story.  When you do, I invite you to contact me.  My intention is that I can help guide you along.   I hope that this will become a community of like minded people.  I invite you to help me understand your needs and together we will keep you moving.  No tricks or fees are involved.   See my <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/about-michael/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"22\">About page</a> for that background.  If you have questions or comments along the way please <a href=\"mailto: MichaelKentBurns@gmail.com\">email me</a>.   This site is a work in progress and I intend to develop it to meet the needs of my readers. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Developing your skills</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While traditional full time employment brings a degree of long term job security, freelancers need to keep their current skills fresh in order to stay relevant.  High tech work is constantly changing with new fields opening up almost daily.  Those new fields often have a higher demand for skilled individuals.  Being willing and able to add new skills will increase your chances of finding work and better pay.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Front end web</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The World Wide Web is a rapidly evolving place, and it is a challenging field to stay fresh in.   Sometimes there are dramatic shifts in interactive technology.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/front-end-web/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"49\">Learn more about front end work...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Back end web</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Back end technologies don\'t change as fast as front end, but...</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/back-end-web/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"52\">Learn more about back end work...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Full stack</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On the surface full stack development is just front end and back end, but there is more to consider...</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/full-stack/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"55\">Learn more about putting it all together...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Working globally</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With the advent of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open-source_software\"><strong>open-source software</strong></a> there arose the need to have world wide access to the source code for the many projects.   <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Git\"><strong>Git</strong></a> is the source control tool invented for Linux development.  <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GitHub\"><strong>GitHub</strong></a> is a web interface for software development which uses Git for the source control features, and describes itself as collaborative version control.   It not only allows you to manage your own projects but lets you share them.  Furthermore it lets you explore a vast galaxy of other projects that you can learn from, and in some cases contribute to.  That is a great way of building your reputation. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/?page_id=59\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"59\">Learn more about how software is developed globally...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Let\'s get acquainted so I can figure out how I can begin to help you. </h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Please take the first challenge to tell me about yourself.  Once we get acquainted I can learn about your needs and desires and continue to develop this site to help you move forward.   I can also get some feedback from you on what is helpful and what is not so much.  Eventually, I would like you to consider being more actively involved in making this site a place where you can help others and learn from them too. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/challenge-tell-me-about-yourself-so-i-know-how-i-can-help-you/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"181\">Take the challenge of introducing your self.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Let\'s consider your development environment</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you are reading this you are probably far enough into web development that you have at least a starter machine and programs to get the work done.    I have a summary of development platforms that you should read to consider what you have, what you might need to move forward.   At the end of that I\'d like to know what you have and what you think you might need.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/development-platforms/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"175\">Learn more about development platforms..</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Take a challenge to <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/challenge-tell-me-about-your-development-setup/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"184\">tell me about your current development setup...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><img class=\"wp-image-420\" style=\"width: 50px;\" src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/New.jpg\" alt=\"\">Software development freelancing activities</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:group {\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>According to <a href=\"https://www.dictionary.com/browse/activity\\\">Dictionary.com an activity</a> is </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item {\"fontSize\":\"small\"} -->\n<li class=\"has-small-font-size\">the <strong>state</strong> or quality of <strong>being active</strong>:</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item {\"fontSize\":\"small\"} -->\n<li class=\"has-small-font-size\"><em>There was not much activity in the stock market today. He doesn\'t have enough physical activity in his life.</em></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item {\"fontSize\":\"small\"} -->\n<li class=\"has-small-font-size\"><strong>a specific deed, action, function, or sphere of action</strong>:<em>social activities.</em></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So, if you want to be a software development freelancer you need these kinds of activities:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Learning</strong>: gaining the knowledge to understand. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Training</strong>: practicing and getting evaluated and coached.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Hiring</strong>: finding a job and establishing a contract.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Planning your work:</strong> figuring out how you are going to do the work, when, and reporting your plan.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Equiping</strong>: getting the tools and platforms needed.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Developing</strong>: building, completing, testing and documenting.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Delivering</strong>: handing it over to your client.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Getting paid</strong>: completing the contract, satisfying the client, and getting the pay you have earned.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Rinse and repeat.</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You <strong>can\'t</strong> do these things by yourself!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>A <strong>learner</strong> needs a <strong>teacher</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>A <strong>trainee</strong> needs a trainer or <strong>mentor</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>A <strong>freelancer</strong> needs a <strong>client</strong> with a <strong>job</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>A <strong>planner</strong> needs many things:  decomposition, stages of work, planning, documenting, reviewing, coordinating...</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Equipping</strong> requires a <strong>source</strong> of tools, platforms, and process knowledge to be ready to do the job.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Developing</strong> is a whole process in itself, covered elsewhere on this site.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Delivery</strong> requires a <strong>repository</strong> to document your process and contain your deliverables so they can be used by the client or others.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Getting paid</strong> requires coordination with the client, an escrow agent, a funds transfer agent, and your bank.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Rinse and repeat</strong> requires <strong>learning</strong> from one job and the <strong>courage</strong> and <strong>determination</strong> to start all over again. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>You can do this!</strong>  This site will lead you to all of these things and you can be a success. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><img class=\"wp-image-420\" style=\"width: 50px;\" src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/New.jpg\" alt=\"\">The internet to the rescue!</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So, where do you find all of these people and things?  There are web based platforms that can supply all of these.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Teaching platforms</strong>: Wikipedia, the WWW, <strong>this site somewhat.</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Training platforms</strong>: FrontendMentor, CodingBootCamp?, <strong>this site</strong>!, Discord, Slack.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Freelancing platforms</strong>: Upwork.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Planning platforms</strong>: Agile alliance, ?</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Equipping platforms</strong>: Google Play, AppStore, Linux \'apt get\', homebrew, many commercial sites. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Development platforms</strong>: GitHub, GitLab, Jira ? </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Delivery platforms</strong>: GitHub, GitLab.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Payment platforms</strong>: Upwork, Payoneer, your bank, mobile apps.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Encouragement platforms</strong>: <strong>this site! </strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Finding work as an individual</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are a number of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Freelancer\">freelance</a> marketplaces online.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.upwork.com/freelance-jobs/\">Upwork</a> is one we recommend.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/finding-work/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"79\">Learn more about freelancing work...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Working as part of a team</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Because of the rapid pace of technology development and market requirements, most web and application development is done by integrated teams.  No one person can do it all themselves. It takes a team of specialists working individually and cross discipline to be successful. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A team can take on big jobs that a single person cannot do.   This presents opportunity for the individual developer.  Once you understand how a team can work together you can find the best place to contribute.   But while you are doing what you already know how to do, you will also learn something about the rest of the team and the roles they fill.   And you will find avenues to learn new skills while you build team skills.   </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/working-in-a-professional-team/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"149\">Learn more about working as part of a larger team ...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Development platforms</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Doing web development work as an individual can be done with most any computer running Windows, Linux, or Macintosh.   You most likely already made a choice and are doing work.   However, as you move into full stack work, or start working as part of a team it will get more complex.   It is worth considering the options again. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So, take a moment to<a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/development-platforms/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"175\"> learn more about development platforms...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Accepting challenges to put your learning to work.</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You may have already encountered a prompt to accept a challenge as you have read this far.  If so, good for you.   I will continue to add more challenges to keep you moving forward.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Learn more from the <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/take-a-challenge/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"178\">complete list of challenges...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to do many things related to this work</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I continue to develop <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/how-to/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"108\">how to pages on simple and more advanced topics.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Latest Posts</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:latest-posts {\"align\":\"center\"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','2-revision-v1','','','2024-05-07 12:48:28','2024-05-07 12:48:28','',2,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?p=423',0,'revision','',0),
(424,1,'2024-05-07 12:53:05','2024-05-07 12:53:05','<!-- wp:group {\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:group {\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:gallery {\"linkTo\":\"none\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"flex\",\"flexWrap\":null}} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\"><!-- wp:image {\"id\":169,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/MichaelAtWork-1024x768.jpeg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-169\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Michael</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":353,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/work-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-353\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Philémon</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></figure>\n<!-- /wp:gallery --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Software development freelancing...</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are many locations around the globe that are hotspots for software development.   If you happen to live in one of those places, jobs can come looking for you.   But there are many places around the world that have little or no jobs in this field.  In those places you need some extra skills to get and keep work, but it can be done.  This site is a place to find help and to build community of fellow developers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Learn a little about me and why I am developing this site on my <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/about-michael/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"22\">About page...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Welcome</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My intention with this main page is to tell a story of a journey that you might be on.  I\'ll try to keep it pretty brief and include \"Learn more...\" links so you can dive deeper as you need.   Hopefully you will find yourself on this journey and find where you are in the story.  When you do, I invite you to contact me.  My intention is that I can help guide you along.   I hope that this will become a community of like minded people.  I invite you to help me understand your needs and together we will keep you moving.  No tricks or fees are involved.   See my <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/about-michael/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"22\">About page</a> for that background.  If you have questions or comments along the way please <a href=\"mailto: MichaelKentBurns@gmail.com\">email me</a>.   This site is a work in progress and I intend to develop it to meet the needs of my readers. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Developing your skills</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While traditional full time employment brings a degree of long term job security, freelancers need to keep their current skills fresh in order to stay relevant.  High tech work is constantly changing with new fields opening up almost daily.  Those new fields often have a higher demand for skilled individuals.  Being willing and able to add new skills will increase your chances of finding work and better pay.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Front end web</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The World Wide Web is a rapidly evolving place, and it is a challenging field to stay fresh in.   Sometimes there are dramatic shifts in interactive technology.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/front-end-web/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"49\">Learn more about front end work...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Back end web</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Back end technologies don\'t change as fast as front end, but...</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/back-end-web/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"52\">Learn more about back end work...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Full stack</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On the surface full stack development is just front end and back end, but there is more to consider...</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/full-stack/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"55\">Learn more about putting it all together...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Working globally</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With the advent of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open-source_software\"><strong>open-source software</strong></a> there arose the need to have world wide access to the source code for the many projects.   <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Git\"><strong>Git</strong></a> is the source control tool invented for Linux development.  <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GitHub\"><strong>GitHub</strong></a> is a web interface for software development which uses Git for the source control features, and describes itself as collaborative version control.   It not only allows you to manage your own projects but lets you share them.  Furthermore it lets you explore a vast galaxy of other projects that you can learn from, and in some cases contribute to.  That is a great way of building your reputation. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/?page_id=59\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"59\">Learn more about how software is developed globally...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Let\'s get acquainted so I can figure out how I can begin to help you. </h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Please take the first challenge to tell me about yourself.  Once we get acquainted I can learn about your needs and desires and continue to develop this site to help you move forward.   I can also get some feedback from you on what is helpful and what is not so much.  Eventually, I would like you to consider being more actively involved in making this site a place where you can help others and learn from them too. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/challenge-tell-me-about-yourself-so-i-know-how-i-can-help-you/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"181\">Take the challenge of introducing your self.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Let\'s consider your development environment</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you are reading this you are probably far enough into web development that you have at least a starter machine and programs to get the work done.    I have a summary of development platforms that you should read to consider what you have, what you might need to move forward.   At the end of that I\'d like to know what you have and what you think you might need.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/development-platforms/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"175\">Learn more about development platforms..</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Take a challenge to <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/challenge-tell-me-about-your-development-setup/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"184\">tell me about your current development setup...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><img class=\"wp-image-420\" style=\"width: 50px;\" src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/New.jpg\" alt=\"\">Software development freelancing activities</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:group {\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>According to <a href=\"https://www.dictionary.com/browse/activity\\\">Dictionary.com an activity</a> is </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item {\"fontSize\":\"small\"} -->\n<li class=\"has-small-font-size\">the <strong>state</strong> or quality of <strong>being active</strong>:</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item {\"fontSize\":\"small\"} -->\n<li class=\"has-small-font-size\"><em>There was not much activity in the stock market today. He doesn\'t have enough physical activity in his life.</em></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item {\"fontSize\":\"small\"} -->\n<li class=\"has-small-font-size\"><strong>a specific deed, action, function, or sphere of action</strong>:<em>social activities.</em></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So, if you want to be a \"<strong>software\"</strong> \"<strong>development\"</strong> \"<strong>freelancer\"</strong> you need these kinds of activities:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Learning</strong>: gaining the knowledge to understand. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Training</strong>: practicing and getting evaluated and coached.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Hiring</strong>: finding a job and establishing a contract.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Planning your work:</strong> figuring out how you are going to do the work, when, and reporting your plan.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Equiping</strong>: getting the tools and platforms needed.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Developing</strong>: building, completing, testing and documenting.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Delivering</strong>: handing it over to your client.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Getting paid</strong>: completing the contract, satisfying the client, and getting the pay you have earned.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Rinse and repeat.</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You <strong>can\'t</strong> do these things by yourself!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>A <strong>learner</strong> needs a <strong>teacher</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>A <strong>trainee</strong> needs a trainer or <strong>mentor</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>A <strong>freelancer</strong> needs a <strong>client</strong> with a <strong>job</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>A <strong>planner</strong> needs many things:  decomposition, stages of work, planning, documenting, reviewing, coordinating...</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Equipping</strong> requires a <strong>source</strong> of tools, platforms, and process knowledge to be ready to do the job.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Developing</strong> is a whole process in itself, covered elsewhere on this site.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Delivery</strong> requires a <strong>repository</strong> to document your process and contain your deliverables so they can be used by the client or others.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Getting paid</strong> requires coordination with the client, an escrow agent, a funds transfer agent, and your bank.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Rinse and repeat</strong> requires <strong>learning</strong> from one job and the <strong>courage</strong> and <strong>determination</strong> to start all over again. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>You can do this!</strong>  This site will lead you to all of these things and you can be a success. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><img class=\"wp-image-420\" style=\"width: 50px;\" src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/New.jpg\" alt=\"\">The internet to the rescue!</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So, where do you find all of these people and things?  There are web based platforms that can supply all of these.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Teaching platforms</strong>: Wikipedia, the WWW, <strong>this site somewhat.</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Training platforms</strong>: FrontendMentor, CodingBootCamp?, <strong>this site</strong>!, Discord, Slack.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Freelancing platforms</strong>: Upwork.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Planning platforms</strong>: Agile alliance, ?</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Equipping platforms</strong>: Google Play, AppStore, Linux \'apt get\', homebrew, many commercial sites. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Development platforms</strong>: GitHub, GitLab, Jira ? </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Delivery platforms</strong>: GitHub, GitLab.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Payment platforms</strong>: Upwork, Payoneer, your bank, mobile apps.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Encouragement platforms</strong>: <strong>this site! </strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Finding work as an individual</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are a number of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Freelancer\">freelance</a> marketplaces online.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.upwork.com/freelance-jobs/\">Upwork</a> is one we recommend.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/finding-work/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"79\">Learn more about freelancing work...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Working as part of a team</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Because of the rapid pace of technology development and market requirements, most web and application development is done by integrated teams.  No one person can do it all themselves. It takes a team of specialists working individually and cross discipline to be successful. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A team can take on big jobs that a single person cannot do.   This presents opportunity for the individual developer.  Once you understand how a team can work together you can find the best place to contribute.   But while you are doing what you already know how to do, you will also learn something about the rest of the team and the roles they fill.   And you will find avenues to learn new skills while you build team skills.   </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/working-in-a-professional-team/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"149\">Learn more about working as part of a larger team ...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Development platforms</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Doing web development work as an individual can be done with most any computer running Windows, Linux, or Macintosh.   You most likely already made a choice and are doing work.   However, as you move into full stack work, or start working as part of a team it will get more complex.   It is worth considering the options again. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So, take a moment to<a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/development-platforms/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"175\"> learn more about development platforms...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Accepting challenges to put your learning to work.</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You may have already encountered a prompt to accept a challenge as you have read this far.  If so, good for you.   I will continue to add more challenges to keep you moving forward.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Learn more from the <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/take-a-challenge/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"178\">complete list of challenges...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to do many things related to this work</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I continue to develop <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/how-to/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"108\">how to pages on simple and more advanced topics.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Latest Posts</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:latest-posts {\"align\":\"center\"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','2-revision-v1','','','2024-05-07 12:53:05','2024-05-07 12:53:05','',2,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?p=424',0,'revision','',0),
(426,1,'2024-05-07 12:54:24','2024-05-07 12:54:24','<!-- wp:group {\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:group {\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:gallery {\"linkTo\":\"none\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"flex\",\"flexWrap\":null}} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\"><!-- wp:image {\"id\":169,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/MichaelAtWork-1024x768.jpeg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-169\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Michael</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":353,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/work-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-353\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Philémon</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></figure>\n<!-- /wp:gallery --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Software development freelancing...</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are many locations around the globe that are hotspots for software development.   If you happen to live in one of those places, jobs can come looking for you.   But there are many places around the world that have little or no jobs in this field.  In those places you need some extra skills to get and keep work, but it can be done.  This site is a place to find help and to build community of fellow developers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Learn a little about me and why I am developing this site on my <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/about-michael/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"22\">About page...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Welcome</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My intention with this main page is to tell a story of a journey that you might be on.  I\'ll try to keep it pretty brief and include \"Learn more...\" links so you can dive deeper as you need.   Hopefully you will find yourself on this journey and find where you are in the story.  When you do, I invite you to contact me.  My intention is that I can help guide you along.   I hope that this will become a community of like minded people.  I invite you to help me understand your needs and together we will keep you moving.  No tricks or fees are involved.   See my <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/about-michael/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"22\">About page</a> for that background.  If you have questions or comments along the way please <a href=\"mailto: MichaelKentBurns@gmail.com\">email me</a>.   This site is a work in progress and I intend to develop it to meet the needs of my readers. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Developing your skills</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While traditional full time employment brings a degree of long term job security, freelancers need to keep their current skills fresh in order to stay relevant.  High tech work is constantly changing with new fields opening up almost daily.  Those new fields often have a higher demand for skilled individuals.  Being willing and able to add new skills will increase your chances of finding work and better pay.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Front end web</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The World Wide Web is a rapidly evolving place, and it is a challenging field to stay fresh in.   Sometimes there are dramatic shifts in interactive technology.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/front-end-web/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"49\">Learn more about front end work...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Back end web</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Back end technologies don\'t change as fast as front end, but...</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/back-end-web/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"52\">Learn more about back end work...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Full stack</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On the surface full stack development is just front end and back end, but there is more to consider...</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/full-stack/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"55\">Learn more about putting it all together...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Working globally</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With the advent of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open-source_software\"><strong>open-source software</strong></a> there arose the need to have world wide access to the source code for the many projects.   <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Git\"><strong>Git</strong></a> is the source control tool invented for Linux development.  <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GitHub\"><strong>GitHub</strong></a> is a web interface for software development which uses Git for the source control features, and describes itself as collaborative version control.   It not only allows you to manage your own projects but lets you share them.  Furthermore it lets you explore a vast galaxy of other projects that you can learn from, and in some cases contribute to.  That is a great way of building your reputation. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/?page_id=59\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"59\">Learn more about how software is developed globally...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Let\'s get acquainted so I can figure out how I can begin to help you. </h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Please take the first challenge to tell me about yourself.  Once we get acquainted I can learn about your needs and desires and continue to develop this site to help you move forward.   I can also get some feedback from you on what is helpful and what is not so much.  Eventually, I would like you to consider being more actively involved in making this site a place where you can help others and learn from them too. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/challenge-tell-me-about-yourself-so-i-know-how-i-can-help-you/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"181\">Take the challenge of introducing your self.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Let\'s consider your development environment</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you are reading this you are probably far enough into web development that you have at least a starter machine and programs to get the work done.    I have a summary of development platforms that you should read to consider what you have, what you might need to move forward.   At the end of that I\'d like to know what you have and what you think you might need.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/development-platforms/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"175\">Learn more about development platforms..</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Take a challenge to <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/challenge-tell-me-about-your-development-setup/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"184\">tell me about your current development setup...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><img class=\"wp-image-420\" style=\"width: 50px;\" src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/New.jpg\" alt=\"\">Software development freelancing activities</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:group {\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>According to <a href=\"https://www.dictionary.com/browse/activity\\\">Dictionary.com an activity</a> is </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item {\"fontSize\":\"small\"} -->\n<li class=\"has-small-font-size\">the <strong>state</strong> or quality of <strong>being active</strong>:</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item {\"fontSize\":\"small\"} -->\n<li class=\"has-small-font-size\"><em>There was not much activity in the stock market today. He doesn\'t have enough physical activity in his life.</em></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item {\"fontSize\":\"small\"} -->\n<li class=\"has-small-font-size\"><strong>a specific deed, action, function, or sphere of action</strong>:<em>social activities.</em></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So, if you want to be a \"<strong>software\"</strong> \"<strong>development\"</strong> \"<strong>freelancer\"</strong> you need these kinds of activities:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Learning</strong>: gaining the knowledge to understand software.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Training</strong>: practicing, getting evaluated and coached.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Hiring</strong>: finding a job and establishing a contract.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Planning your work:</strong> figuring out how you are going to do the work, when, and reporting your plan.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Equiping</strong>: getting the tools and platforms needed.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Developing</strong>: building, completing, testing and documenting.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Delivering</strong>: handing it over to your client.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Getting paid</strong>: completing the contract, satisfying the client, and getting the pay you have earned.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Rinse and repeat.</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You <strong>can\'t</strong> do these things by yourself!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>A <strong>learner</strong> needs a <strong>teacher</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>A <strong>trainee</strong> needs a trainer or <strong>mentor</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>A <strong>freelancer</strong> needs a <strong>client</strong> with a <strong>job</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>A <strong>planner</strong> needs many things:  decomposition, stages of work, planning, documenting, reviewing, coordinating...</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Equipping</strong> requires a <strong>source</strong> of tools, platforms, and process knowledge to be ready to do the job.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Developing</strong> is a whole process in itself, covered elsewhere on this site.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Delivery</strong> requires a <strong>repository</strong> to document your process and contain your deliverables so they can be used by the client or others.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Getting paid</strong> requires coordination with the client, an escrow agent, a funds transfer agent, and your bank.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Rinse and repeat</strong> requires <strong>learning</strong> from one job and the <strong>courage</strong> and <strong>determination</strong> to start all over again. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>You can do this!</strong>  This site will lead you to all of these things and you can be a success. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><img class=\"wp-image-420\" style=\"width: 50px;\" src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/New.jpg\" alt=\"\">The internet to the rescue!</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So, where do you find all of these people and things?  There are web based platforms that can supply all of these.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Teaching platforms</strong>: Wikipedia, the WWW, <strong>this site somewhat.</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Training platforms</strong>: FrontendMentor, CodingBootCamp?, <strong>this site</strong>!, Discord, Slack.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Freelancing platforms</strong>: Upwork.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Planning platforms</strong>: Agile alliance, ?</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Equipping platforms</strong>: Google Play, AppStore, Linux \'apt get\', homebrew, many commercial sites. </li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Development platforms</strong>: GitHub, GitLab, Jira, Gerrit ?</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Delivery platforms</strong>: GitHub, GitLab, AppStore, Google Play.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Payment platforms</strong>: Upwork, Payoneer, your bank, mobile apps.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Encouragement platforms</strong>: <strong>this site! </strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Finding work as an individual</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are a number of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Freelancer\">freelance</a> marketplaces online.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.upwork.com/freelance-jobs/\">Upwork</a> is one we recommend.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/finding-work/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"79\">Learn more about freelancing work...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Working as part of a team</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Because of the rapid pace of technology development and market requirements, most web and application development is done by integrated teams.  No one person can do it all themselves. It takes a team of specialists working individually and cross discipline to be successful. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A team can take on big jobs that a single person cannot do.   This presents opportunity for the individual developer.  Once you understand how a team can work together you can find the best place to contribute.   But while you are doing what you already know how to do, you will also learn something about the rest of the team and the roles they fill.   And you will find avenues to learn new skills while you build team skills.   </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/working-in-a-professional-team/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"149\">Learn more about working as part of a larger team ...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Development platforms</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Doing web development work as an individual can be done with most any computer running Windows, Linux, or Macintosh.   You most likely already made a choice and are doing work.   However, as you move into full stack work, or start working as part of a team it will get more complex.   It is worth considering the options again. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So, take a moment to<a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/development-platforms/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"175\"> learn more about development platforms...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Accepting challenges to put your learning to work.</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You may have already encountered a prompt to accept a challenge as you have read this far.  If so, good for you.   I will continue to add more challenges to keep you moving forward.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Learn more from the <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/take-a-challenge/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"178\">complete list of challenges...</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to do many things related to this work</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I continue to develop <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/how-to/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"108\">how to pages on simple and more advanced topics.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Latest Posts</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:latest-posts {\"align\":\"center\"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','2-revision-v1','','','2024-05-07 12:54:24','2024-05-07 12:54:24','',2,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?p=426',0,'revision','',0),
(428,1,'2024-05-07 20:37:15','2024-05-07 20:37:15','<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/how-to/how-to-contribute-to-this-site/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"115\">Contribute to this site</a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><img class=\"wp-image-420\" style=\"width: 30px;\" src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/New.jpg\" alt=\"\"><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/how-to/how-to-do-easy-time-estimates/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"404\">How To Do Easy Time Estimates</a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/how-to-administer-a-wordpress-site/\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/how-to-administer-a-wordpress-site/\">WordPress administrative tasks</a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Cloudways hosting administration tasks:</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Find your way around this site:</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/using-xampp-for-development-work/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"247\">Install a full stack on your local development computer</a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->','How to ...','','inherit','closed','closed','','108-revision-v1','','','2024-05-07 20:37:15','2024-05-07 20:37:15','',108,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?p=428',0,'revision','',0),
(429,1,'2024-05-07 20:38:42','2024-05-07 20:38:42','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><img class=\"wp-image-420\" style=\"width: 30px;\" src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/New.jpg\" alt=\"\">One of the most critical and least successful parts of software development is estimating how long a project is going to take and meeting those estimates.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Long ago projects were small and done by small teams of highly motivated engineers. They had an idea of something good to build and they just dove in and started writing code. These were the pioneering days and most of these projects are called <strong><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skunkworks_project\">skunk-works projects</a>.</strong> They often worked long hours and did not tell anyone what they built until it worked. Some famous projects were <strong>UNIX</strong>, <strong>Linux</strong>, the <strong>Macintosh Personal Computer</strong>, and other little things.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, as time went on and people started paying big money for big computers and needed big complex software, the whole process got big and complicated. Lots of money was raised, lots of people were hired, and customers were anxious to get the final product. This meant that you had to make promises of functionality and set dates for delivery. This meant that a lot of success was riding on getting it right. This was the era of the <strong><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Waterfall_model\">waterfall method</a> </strong>of project planning. These projects costs many millions of dollars and often took many years to build. IBM was THE BIG player in such projects. They would often start several teams in different places of the world and give them all the same project. That caused a lot of competition between the teams. This is because as some teams fell behind their project was cancelled and the people often fired. In the end one team was selected as the victor. Many of these large projects involved multiple companies collaborating, and the end result was often gigantic failures.  Some examples are the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multics\">Multics</a> operating system, and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taligent\">Taligent</a>.  I\'ll bet you have never heard of either of them. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There were a handful of pioneers that decided there had to be a better way of project planning. One of the results of those efforts became a group of methods under the umbrella term<strong> <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Agile_software_development\">Agile Software Development</a>.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are two stories I wish to share that are a quick introduction to Agile techniques.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">The Chicken and the Pig</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.michaelvizdos.com/resources/scrum-chicken-pig-cartoon-origin\">The cartoon: </a> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One day <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Chicken_and_the_Pig\"><strong>a Chicken and a Pig</strong></a> decided they would open a restaurant together. As they each decided what they could contribute to the effort it became clear that they were very different from each other in their investment. The chicken pointed out that she could lay eggs almost every day, and with her fellow chickens they could bring fresh eggs to cook every day. However, when the pig volunteered its ham, he realized that his and his friends investment was a one time all in investment.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What this funny story shows is that the \"boss\" or project sponsor has a small investment and he can have many projects some of which might succeed and some might fail.   However, the workers that worked full time on the project were investing their very livelihoods and all of their time.   </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The agile moral of this story is that the boss gets to decide what the project should build and how it needs to function for the customer, but his interest stops there.  His job is to hire a team that are qualified to do the job, guide them along the way, and get them the resources they need to do the job.   </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The team however, gets to determine how they will organize the work, plan the schedule, and get the job done.  They are day to day, week by week, coordinating and working together as best they can to get it done on time and to requirements.    </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Gummy Bears</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gummy_bear\">Gummy Bears are a favorite snack of children and software engineers. </a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Many of the early agile teams wanted a quick and easy way to make rough estimates of the work required and how best to organize the effort.  They wanted to spend only a little time on the estimate and then simply get to work.   As they worked they kept rough track of the time spent on each task they had estimated and after every week or two (called a sprint like in Rugby) they took a few minutes to reflect on the sprint and their estimates versus actuals.   The idea is to slowly get better and better at estimating the effort for small pieces of the work so they could more accurately plan and finish small to large parts of the overall project.   Each sprint they get better and learn more.  That makes the next sprint planning meeting much quicker and more accurate.   </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One particular team always had a bowl of gummy bears on the table when they had their planning meetings.  So everybody grabbed a handful and put them on the table in front of themselves.    As they considered each task they would each put a certain number of bears out in front (like poker) and then explained why they thought that task was easy or hard to do.   After everybody made their bid, the team came to a quick agreement and assigned a number (usually between 1 and 7 bears) to a task.  Then they moved on.  The whole meeting goes pretty quick and soon they have a set of tasks to do in the sprint and assign those to capable engineers.    Done. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Why something silly? Well many teams got a little more formal and ended up calling them \"<a href=\"https://www.agilealliance.org/glossary/points-estimates-in/\"><strong>Story Points</strong></a>\". The main idea is that it is a concept that each team uses to judge relative difficulty based on what they are capable of . You DON\'T want to use some real unit of time (like hours or days or weeks). Because once you do that, you have driven a stake in the ground and committed yourself to actually getting it done on that schedule. This leads to short cuts, burn out, and slipped schedules.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So, what does it really mean to the team?  That is up to the team.  They have their own way of relating the effort for a specific task based on what similar tasks have been in their past.   Also, what ends up happening is that since their knowledge of the tasks grows and they get quicker at understanding and finishing tasks, they find out that they are getting faster at getting the tasks done.  We call this \"team velocity\".   As they get better they can get more gummy bears or story points done in a single sprint.    This is a very rewarding and motivating way of planning.  It is empowering.   The alternative of setting hard deadlines and then missing them or getting done too early is very de-motivating.    </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Much more to come...</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->','How To Do Easy Time Estimates','','inherit','closed','closed','','404-revision-v1','','','2024-05-07 20:38:42','2024-05-07 20:38:42','',404,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?p=429',0,'revision','',0),
(430,1,'2024-05-07 21:16:15','2024-05-07 21:16:15','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Today is a big day in the history of this effort for several reasons!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Our first cohort #1 has now finished the introductory challenges and are ready to work as a team.</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"small\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-small-font-size\">Meet Philémon , Destin , and Efatha .</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"linkTo\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\"><!-- wp:image {\"id\":397,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/ash-picture-1024x875.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-397\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Ashuza </figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":358,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Efatha.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-358\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Efatha</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":353,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/work-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-353\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Philémon</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></figure>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Two of our members have also finished projects that are important contributions to this site.  </h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"small\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-small-font-size\">Philémon made major updates to the <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/front-end-web/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"49\">front-end web</a> page, while Destin made major additions to our <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/full-stack/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"55\">full stack page</a>. Each of them successfully planned their project and executed it on time and according to budget. I was somewhat surprised that they each made good estimates and worked accordingly. They have learned a lot about agile methods without knowing what agile methods are. Good job guys!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Together the three of them are now embarking on their very own self managed team project.   </h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"small\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-small-font-size\">With Philémon as team lead, the three of them are currently in the kickoff phase of their very own project.  When they are well underway we will announce the GitHub repository where you can see their work as it progresses.  There will also be a public demo site that you can see it in action.   Stay tuned...    When complete, it will likely be incorporated as a new feature of this mentoring site satisfying an outstanding enhancement issue. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"small\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-small-font-size\">They are currently getting oriented to their new project and are in a one week training iteration in order to begin to learn the important Agile development methods they will need to succeed.   Some new additions to this site are featured on the <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"2\">Home page</a>, and a new How to... page <a href=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/index.php/how-to/how-to-do-easy-time-estimates/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"404\">How To Do Easy Time Estimates</a>.   You will be able to spot those new sections by the marker graphic <img class=\"wp-image-420\" style=\"width: 50px;\" src=\"https://michaelkentburns.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/New.jpg\" alt=\"\"></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"small\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-small-font-size\">The other part of their training is getting oriented to the use of a common Github repository that they each will clone and work on.  Each will have separate \"Issues\" managed in the central repository.   They will plan those issues as a team in weekly scrum meetings, and then each of them will decompose those larger \"story\" issues into smaller \"task\" issues.  As each task is completed they will commit the code, test cases, and documentation to the main branch and then push it to the common repository.   There the whole team will be able to review and guide each other\'s efforts to make maximum use of the skills of all.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Please!  If you read this post, leave a comment to let us know and congratulate our new team.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Post 4: A Big Celebration!','','publish','open','open','','a-big-celebration','','','2024-11-01 07:42:25','2024-11-01 07:42:25','',0,'https://michaelkentburns.com/?p=430',0,'post','',2),
